<headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 12 at 10:10AM EST  by NWS Albany</headline>
<description>...Heavy Snow Developing This Morning into This Afternoon...
Heavy snow developing across the Glens Falls Saratoga region,
Taconics, Berkshires, Litchfield Hills and southern Vermont, will
continue through this morning and into this afternoon. Snowfall
rates of 1 to 2 inches per hour will lead to snow covered roads
and poor visibility. This includes the Northway from the Capital
District northward and the Berkshire Spur of the New York State
Thruway. Avoid unnecessary travel if possible, as conditions will
quickly become hazardous.</description>
